    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think we need to disable all keyboard shortcuts in widgets. Otherwise we\nwill inevitably conflict with keyboard shortcuts in widgets. Put another\nway, as a matter of policy, the widget keyboard namespace needs to be empty\nand reserved entirely for widget authors.\n\nOn Tue, Feb 11, 2014 at 10:05 AM, Thomas Kluyver\nnotifications@github.comwrote:\n\n> I can reproduce the ctrl+s issue - I guess we disable all shortcuts when\n> we're in a text editor, but a few are actually still safe.\n> \n> I can't reproduce the issue with hitting escape after searching for\n> something, either on Firefox or Chromium. If someone else can, please open\n> a separate issue for that.\n> \n> ## \n> \n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHubhttps://github.com/ipython/ipython/issues/5079#issuecomment-34785192\n> .\n\n## \n\nBrian E. Granger\nCal Poly State University, San Luis Obispo\nbgranger@calpoly.edu and ellisonbg@gmail.com\n"
  },
